## Using Advanced Techniques Effectively

### Building Momentum for Activation

Advanced techniques require +3 Momentum, which you accumulate through:

**Aggressive Stance:** Generate +1 Momentum per successful attack. Three hits builds enough Momentum.

**Balanced Stance:** Generate +1 Momentum on rolls of 10+. Consistent excellence builds reserves.

**Defensive Stance:** Generate +1 Momentum when attacked. Being targeted builds activation opportunities.

Plan several turns ahead. Don't spend Momentum carelessly on minor techniques when advanced technique activation is close.

### Timing Your Activation

Advanced techniques feel climactic when used at critical moments:

**Turn the tide:** Activate when combat shifts against you—Whirlwind Strike eliminates surrounding enemies, Perfect Parry negates devastating attack.

**Finish fights:** Activate when enemies cluster or priority targets expose themselves—Devastating Blow ends climactic encounters.

**Enable combos:** Activate to set up party coordination—skill mastery succeeds at crucial check, team coordination empowers entire party.

Don't waste advanced techniques on trivial encounters. Save them for moments that matter.

### Choosing Which Techniques to Learn

At moderate milestones, select techniques that:

**Fill capability gaps:** Combat specialists take skill techniques for versatility. Wizards take combat techniques for survival.

**Enhance existing strengths:** Fighters double down on combat devastation. Skill experts guarantee critical successes.

**Enable signature strategies:** Build around specific playstyles—area specialists take Whirlwind Strike, defense experts take Perfect Parry.

You'll learn 3-4 advanced techniques across typical campaigns. Choose carefully—each represents major milestone investment.

### Combining with Other Techniques

Advanced techniques work alongside basic techniques and class abilities:

**Layer effects:** Perfect Parry (advanced) + Riposte (basic) = negate attack then counterattack
**Sequence actions:** Whirlwind Strike (advanced) hits all enemies, generate Momentum, use basic techniques with new Momentum
**Multiply benefits:** Cast 2 Spells (advanced) + Metamagic (wizard feature) = two enhanced spells simultaneously

Advanced techniques are capstones, not replacements. Master basic techniques first, then add advanced options for tactical depth.

